    <sect1 id="quickstart.sect.prerequisites.install">
        <title>Prerequisites for Installation</title>
        <para>&susemgr; 3 requires that you have created an account with &scc;. During installation
            of &susemgr; &scc; credentials will be requested and you must enter them to receive the
            latest packages and updates. The following procedure will guide you through obtaining
            your &scc;<systemitem>Organizational Credentials</systemitem></para>

        <procedure id="creating.scc.account.mgr">
            <title>Obtaining Your &scc; Organization Credentials</title>
            <step>
                <para>Open a browser and direct it to: <ulink url="https://scc.suse.com/login"
                    /></para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>If you have not done so, create an account now.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Log in to your new &scc; account.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Under the <systemitem>Management tools</systemitem> widget select
                        <systemitem>Manage Users</systemitem>.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Click on the <systemitem>Organization Credentials</systemitem> tab. </para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Keep this information handy during &susemgr; 3 setup.</para>
            </step>
        </procedure>

        <para>This completes &susemgr; installation prerequisites.</para>

    </sect1>

    <sect1 id="quickstart.sect.software.requirements">
        <title>&susemgr; 3 Requirements</title>
        <para>The following section provides information covering &susemgr; hardware, supported
            clients, and database requirements.</para>
        <sect2 id="table.manager.requirements.server">
            <title>Server Requirements</title>
            <informaltable>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="1*"/>
                    <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="4*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para> Hardware </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para> Required/Recommended </para>
                            </entry>
                            
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para> CPU </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para> Required: a multi-core 64bit CPU (x86_64). </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para> RAM </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para> Required: 4&nbsp;GB when only managing a few client systems. </para>
                                <para> Recommended for production use: 16&nbsp;GB. </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para> Free Disk Space </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para> Required: 40&nbsp;GB for &sle; 12 SP1 base installation. </para>
                                <para> Required: 30&nbsp;GB for /var/lib/pgsql (Created by default
                                    during &sle; 12 Installation </para>
                                <para>Required: 100&nbsp;GB for /var/spacewalk (Created by default
                                    during &susemgr; Setup for &suse; channel storage)</para>

                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </informaltable>

        </sect2>
